r>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/7/03 10:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2739.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   1hs vs. 2hs</span><hr size=1> Please correct any information I may be wrong about...<br>
<br>
The way I understand taunt to work (from reading on these boards) is that Taunt is a mixture of the warrior pressing the taunt key and other weapon factors such as delay and damage.  So I am trying to determine when to be using my 2hs vs. my 1hs.<br>
<br>
I am currently wielding a Winter's Fury in Primary, and Jagged Blade of Mourning in Secondary.  I have a Black Acrylia Halberd for 2hs.<br>
<br>
I have 2 questions:  <br>
<br>
If I am not the MT in a raid or xp group, should I switch to the 2hs since it is lower delay?  <br>
<br>
And also, according to common knowledge about damage calculation, will I do more damage with the 2hs than dual wielding my 1hs's?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance. <p>Sanori Maximus<br>
55th Myrmidon<br>
Druzzil Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daxos92>Daxos92</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/7/03 12:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2739.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 1hs vs. 2hs</span><hr size=1> Well, when we're talking about weapons and &quot;Taunt&quot;, using the Taunt skill really has nothing to do with it. It's just a measure of how well a particular weapon setup's combination of dps and procs work to piss mobs off and keep you at the top of the hate list with as little effort as possible by the group.<br>
<br>
Take Taunting Blow for example.... you gain 450 hate points every time a weapon with that effect procs (on top of the damage you're already doing). In order for a weapon setup with no procs whatsoever to out-aggro that, you'd basically have to deal out damage faster than the warrior's DPS plus however fast those +450 procs are going off.<br>
<br>
You'll see if you take a peek at the &quot;top aggro weapons&quot; thread in the equipment forum, there are only really a few types of procs that are particularly good at generating aggro - <br>
Pure +hate (enraging blow etc)<br>
Stuns<br>
Slows<br>
Debuffs<br>
<br>
Procs that only do DD (fleshgrinder's Combust) are good for boosting your damage, but generally not so great if all you're looking for is to keep a mob taunted.<br>
<br>
That said, it doesn't really become necessary to start keeping those high-aggro weapons handy until the high end game. Most tanks can keep aggro just fine by trying to maximize their damage output and learning how groups can control mobs up to the 50s.<br>
<br>
Edit - heh, got a little off topic there I guess and didn't actually answer your question. I would personally use your Black Acrylia Halberd in most situations, as a 40/48 two hander with lifetap proc should outdamage your current 1h setup by a pretty noticable amount <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=443380" target="_blank">Daxos Valdorn</a><br>
62 Warlord<br>
Ayonae Ro<br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daxos92>Daxos92</A> at: 1/7/03 12:26:34 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sanorimaximus>SanoriMaximus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/7/03 12:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2739.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 1hs vs. 2hs</span><hr size=1> Ok thanks for the info...<br>
<br>
Let me rephrase my question though.  If I am using my Black Acrylia Halberd, will I generate more or less aggro than my 1hs set up?<br>
<br>
I know now that my BAH will outdamage the 1hs setup, but because of the higher delay, will it be sufficent for MT duties?  I realize there is a balance between DPS, swing time, procs, and hitting the taunt button to generate aggro; so I am wondering if the increased damage of the BAH will suffice for the increased delay compared to the low delay of my 1hs setup.<br>
<br>
As a side note, what's a good way to get my 2hs maxed?  I don't have access to a shaman, just a 52 druid.  And will I get skillups as often on light blues as compared to dark blues?  I was thinking of going to OOT seafuries since they hit very low and have high hp and are still light blue/dark blue to me.<br>
<br>
Thanks again in advance. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daxos92>Daxos92</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 100<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/7/03 4:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2739.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 1hs vs. 2hs</span><hr size=1> I've been tanking with my 44 delay two-hander lately and haven't had any aggro problems, the best advice I can give ya is just try both setups and see which one seems to hold taunt the best.<br>
<br>
Odds are you won't see any skill increases at all against light blue cons. It happens every now and then, but not often. Fight dark blues and higher to get your skills up (dex buffs help, but not completely necessary).<br>
<br>
 <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=443380" target="_blank">Daxos Valdorn</a><br>
62 Warlord<br>
Ayonae Ro<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/7/03 9:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2739.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 1hs vs. 2hs</span><hr size=1> Without counting procs the weapon with better ratio will always outtaunt the weapons with lesser ratio.  Of course, how the game compares ratio of 1H versus 2H is somewhat of a mystery.  Like others have suggested, the easiest way to tell is by parsing.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilaara>Kilaara</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 198<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/03 5:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2739.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 1hs vs. 2hs</span><hr size=1> The problem is more damage = more aggro against more hits = more aggro.<br>
<br>
It is possible that you can hold aggro as good with your halberd as you can do it with your 1hers.<br>
<br>
But.<br>
<br>
When you miss 8 times in a row ( dont say it can't happen ), which would be around 5 rounds of combat with your 2her in the Beginning of your battle you will generate nearly no aggro. That is the time in which your chanter maybe has some trouble . When you miss 8 times in a row with your 1hers its around 2 and a bit rounds of combat in which you generate more aggro from the hits as in same amount of time with the 2her. <br>
<br>
The 1hers give you a constant flow of aggro. The 2her give you more aggro spikes.<br>
<br>
Last I was in group with a BoC/Ichoflor (Primal ) wielding warrior and was using Primal 2h/TSBS and from time to time in fight or at start I grabbed aggro without taunting cause of some nice series of 300* hits.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:lime;font-size:x-small;">Da Basherle</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4552"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:gold;font-size:small;">Kilaara Drachenfliege</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;">Drachentänzer</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Solusek Ro</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khanktinga>khanktinga</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/03 7:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2739.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 1hs vs. 2hs</span><hr size=1> Something else to consider for the high end game, when you tank mobs that hit for 300+, is the riposte factor. The fact is, more attacks by you = more ripostes for the mob. Dual wielding fast weapons against Tier 2+ mobs is going to add some extra pain, so I would only do so when you really need the extra taunt and/or stats from your 1h combo. I don't think I lose that much taunting ability tanking in PoValor when using a windblade vs. FG/Red epic combo, but I do see a significant boost in how much riposte damage I take. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://plaza.ufl.edu/ktinga/eqimages/OlavnBalth2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=193443">Olav's Stuff</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=176430">Balth's Kunk-fu Gear</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 81<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/8/03 5:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2739.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 1hs vs. 2hs</span><hr size=1> The damage you actually dish out has next to no significance on aggro.  Otherwise it'd be more than twice as hard to get aggro under defensive and this is certainly not the case while tanking (aggro doesn't suddenly become easier when defensive runs out).  When I was practicing 2H Blunt I managed to steal aggro with attacks that are either miss or crush for minimum damage (and no taunting of course).  If aggro is related to damage even significantly this would not be possible at all.  Each time you swing your weaopn at something it generates aggro that's related to the base damage of the weapon regardless of whether you actually hit something or not.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kazzuk>Kazzuk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/9/03 9:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2739.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RE: 1hs vs 2hs</span><hr size=1> Incorrect Phantron,<br>
<br>
Damage has a dirtect bearing on where you get placed on the hate list, if ya don't believe me, ask a monk/ranger/wizard. Or even beter, use a high dmg non procing 2 hander like a TSBS or even a Windblade.<br>
<br>
Aggro type procs and the Taunt skill has a more noticable (i.e neckbreak turning <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) effect on aggro but it is ALL cumulative. And yes, missess also add aggro, otherwise pulling with a bow for a war would be damned near useless (hehe).<br>
<br>
As far as defensive goes... it depends on your weapon setup. Go defensive early on an easier raid type mob to tank like say Vindi, you will find you need to tank him solo a bit longer until you get that aggro locking proc, etc or you will loose aggro to your monks, rogues, etc or cause them to nerf their dps considerably to help you keep aggro (a bad thing). It has also been speculated that being defensive in its self incurrs some aggro as the mob is getting pissed that it cannot hit you quite right Again, this is total speculation. I myself NEVER have had an agro problem while defensive with SK aggro buffs, I rarely ever loose aggro until I try to (and even then sometimes cant <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) and have another tank take it with AT during tank switch. So maybe there is some truth to that speculation.<br>
<br>
Also, I find aggro quite often becomes easier to grab when defensive runs out.... its called low life aggro LOL. But seriously, think about that, once defensive is gone, you hit more often, more often you hit, more likely you are to proc. Also you aren't taking the 45% penalty to dmg (the misses) thus get more dmg based hate as well.<br>
<br>
This is based on my own parses of defensive, i.e. I seem to hit for less and miss alot more often while defensive, but still swing just as often... that seems to be the price we pay for curtting the damage we take pretty much in half <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaylonn>Gaylonn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/9/03 10:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2739.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://bellsouthpwp.net/R/a/RafaelSmith/axe.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RE: 1hs vs 2hs</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>The damage you actually dish out has next to no significance on aggro<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
From my relatively &quot;newbie&quot; opinion, this is just not true.<br>
<br>
Although I have yet to tank anything significant, I have finally ventured out into the PoP with some guildies and raw DPS of my Windblade out-aggros anthing else I or anyone else my group have.  <br>
