<br>
I love weapon debates.<br>
<br>
Okay...I hunt mainly in Pop zones now so this is what I would suggest.<br>
<br>
Take a warrior with 2 fast weapons one of them a &quot;hate&quot; weapon and put him in group with a warrior using a nice damaging 2 handed weapon.<br>
<br>
I have done this in caves in pov and the 2 handed weapon twisted steel bastard sword I have out aggroed the other warrior with 2 fast 1 handed (one of them a 450 hate weapon).<br>
<br>
But let me add this.<br>
<br>
The other warrior had all defensive AA and no offensive AA to work with those 2 1 handed weapons.  He was a 64 warrior and I was 62.<br>
<br>
I had the following AA Skills working with my 2 handed twisted steel bastard sword.<br>
combat fury 3 trainings<br>
flurry 3 trainings<br>
ferocity 1 training<br>
fury of the ages 1 training<br>
punishing blade 1 training<br>
<br>
With the above skills I was dishing out quite a large dps 120dps with the twisted steel bastard sword.<br>
<br>
I did not lose aggro once to the other warrior.<br>
<br>
So the amount of damage (especially in pop) does have a lot to do with keeping aggro.  In PoP you have to kill fast and hard or you will die fast and hard.<br>
<br>
I am not disagreeing with what hate weapons can do.  They can still help an MT catch aggro real fast but (without the proper offensive AA skills to back them up an MT without some offensive AA skills and other needs on list below with those hate weapons) won't hold aggro.<br>
<br>
Remember LEVEL +  AA SKILLS +  WEAPONS +  HASTE = DAMAGE = ONE TICKED OFF MOB = AGGRO<br>
<br>
Not just weapons.<br>
Not just AA skills.<br>
Not just levels.<br>
Not just haste.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps,<br>
Gigantuous - 62 Warlord of Povar <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=thegiantone>TheGiantOne</A> at: 1/9/03 11:45:07 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tashi6>Tashi6</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/9/03 11:48 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2739.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RE: 1hs vs 2hs</span><hr size=1> I have not done any real tests on this, but here is how I think it works:<br>
<br>
Damage/Dly ratio of your weapon is used for how much hate you generate per swing.  (miss, hit, whatever)<br>
<br>
Damage actually done is added to this.  This doens't seem to as much of a factor as the above, but raw damage has to increase hate somewhat.  It would be hard to believe that somone who misses 10 times in a row would have the same hate as somone who hit for max damage 10 times in a row using the same weapon. But...  Misses = agro too ;-)   As people have said, being defensive/evasive doesn't seem to make it hard to hold agro...<br>
<br>
<br>
So, ignoring procs, simple way to figure out what weapon/weapon combo will give you the most agro is to parse DPS, or just comapre dmg/dly ratio.  The reason i'd go with a parse is that the dmg/dly for 1h vs 2h is not so easy to compare like that.<br>
<br>
Parse DPS while tanking.. not just hitting something.  Take AA and ripostes into account.  Use a slower 2hander for example, you will take less riposte damage,  and do more riposte damage in return (moreso with double riposte AA).  Each riposte YOU send at a mob = agro as well, and a single extra swing from a riposte wiht a big fat 2hander is much much more significant a hit from a dual wield combo. This may not be so big a deal, but it surely is another advantage of 2h, especially with the double riposte AA which is basically uselss with dual wield.<br>
<br>
Procs complicate things,<br>
 Just how many swings/points of damage is an enraging blow proc worth?  <br>
<br>
Or, how much hate does EB give compared to a stun+dd proc?<br>
EB is no resist, but resisted spells like slows/mezs/stuns still piss mobs off the same.. resist or no resist.. so thats not really an issue in my opinion.<br>
<br>
<br>
How much better would a weapon with no proc at all have to be vs an EB proc weapon to generate equal average hate over a period of time?<br>
<br>
Would have to do some extensive testing to answer those questions, but IMO.. 2h &gt; 1h <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
